WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.500
We're continuing in our series, coming to the end of it, of Firm Foundation, where we're

2
00:00:05.500 --> 00:00:08.740
looking at our church statement of faith together.

3
00:00:08.740 --> 00:00:14.420
And last Sunday we looked at our statement on the church, and this Sunday we're continuing

4
00:00:14.420 --> 00:00:15.420
with that.

5
00:00:15.420 --> 00:00:21.000
So last Sunday we really focused on who the church is, or what the church is.

6
00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.660
And this Sunday we're focusing on the practices of the church, so what the church

7
00:00:24.660 --> 00:00:26.760
does.

8
00:00:26.760 --> 00:00:34.040
And we've been looking at Acts chapter 2 verses 41 to 47, and so we're going to read that

9
00:00:34.040 --> 00:00:35.040
again this morning.

10
00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:46.280
Acts chapter 2 verses 41 to 47 says, So those who received his word were baptized, and they

11
00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:49.880
were added that day about 3,000 souls.

12
00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:54.680
And they devoted themselves to the apostles' teaching and the fellowship, to the breaking

13
00:00:54.680 --> 00:00:57.080
of bread and the prayers.

14
00:00:57.080 --> 00:01:03.780
And all came upon every soul, and many wonders and signs were being done through the apostles,

15
00:01:03.780 --> 00:01:08.200
and all who believed were together and had all things in common.

16
00:01:08.200 --> 00:01:12.240
And they were selling their possessions and belongings and distributing the proceeds

17
00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:14.400
to all as any had need.

18
00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:20.320
And day by day, attending the temple together and breaking bread in their homes, they received

19
00:01:20.320 --> 00:01:23.560
their food with glad and generous hearts.

20
00:01:23.560 --> 00:01:28.920
And God, in having favor with all the people, and the Lord added to their number day by

21
00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:32.040
day those who were being saved.

22
00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:35.960
This is the word of the Lord.

23
00:01:35.960 --> 00:01:42.680
Years ago I read an interesting book called Tribe by Sebastian Younger.

24
00:01:42.680 --> 00:01:46.320
And it's essentially a book, it's not a Christian book, he's not a believer, but it's a

25
00:01:46.320 --> 00:01:53.040
book about the importance of living in community as opposed to living in isolation.

26
00:01:53.040 --> 00:01:58.520
And in the book, Younger points to various studies that show that, particularly that

27
00:01:58.520 --> 00:02:04.480
deep social bonds often form in high stakes environments.

28
00:02:04.480 --> 00:02:09.580
So these social bonds, they form when you're in a kind of a threatening environment together,

29
00:02:09.580 --> 00:02:13.800
and there people devote their energy to the good of the community rather than just

30
00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.720
themselves.

31
00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:19.440
So he gives battlefields as an example.

32
00:02:19.440 --> 00:02:26.360
Wounds are a terrible place to be, but they often produce a depth of camaraderie that people

33
00:02:26.360 --> 00:02:30.840
struggle to find in other places.

34
00:02:30.840 --> 00:02:37.000
And he notes how difficult it can be to go from experiencing that kind of level of brotherhood

35
00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:45.920
that shared experience, that shared purpose to then living in a modern world as a civilian

36
00:02:45.920 --> 00:02:54.560
in a place where you're in a culture where isolating self-sufficiency is the name of the

37
00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:59.920
game rather than living in an interdependent community.

38
00:02:59.920 --> 00:03:05.440
Last week we saw that we longed for community because we were created for community.

39
00:03:05.440 --> 00:03:11.000
We were designed for fellowship with God and fellowship with one another.

40
00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:16.560
And we were made to experience that life together in the fellowship of the church.

41
00:03:16.560 --> 00:03:22.480
You see the church is designed to be a place where we experience true community, joining

42
00:03:22.480 --> 00:03:26.120
together with a shared purpose.

43
00:03:26.120 --> 00:03:31.880
Of course we have to admit that the church doesn't always live up to that, and that

44
00:03:31.880 --> 00:03:34.600
includes this one as well.

45
00:03:34.600 --> 00:03:38.360
Nevertheless, it's what we're made for.

46
00:03:38.360 --> 00:03:44.200
God is present and at work in us to bring about that kind of community.

47
00:03:44.200 --> 00:03:48.640
In Acts chapter two where we're looking, we just to remind us God has poured out His spirit

48
00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:55.160
upon His church, and the kind of community that emerges is remarkable.

49
00:03:55.160 --> 00:04:00.240
And when you look at this community here, it gives us something to aim for together,

50
00:04:00.240 --> 00:04:06.280
but more than that it shows us what happens when we are led by God's Spirit to become

51
00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:09.840
the kind of people He has created us to be.

52
00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:14.480
So yeah, we've got a wonderful aim here, but this is primarily saying, look, this is what

53
00:04:14.480 --> 00:04:15.480
God is doing.

54
00:04:15.480 --> 00:04:19.200
And if you're led by His Spirit and walking in step with His Spirit, this is the kind

55
00:04:19.200 --> 00:04:25.760
of thing that happens in your midst as a community of believers, as a church.

56
00:04:25.760 --> 00:04:29.720
Well any group that you step into, you might wonder, like, what do I have in common

57
00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:30.720
with these people?

58
00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:33.360
Maybe even look around the room today and think, what do I actually have in common

59
00:04:33.360 --> 00:04:36.080
with the folks who are here?

60
00:04:36.080 --> 00:04:40.520
And what I want to draw out is three things that we share in common together.

61
00:04:40.520 --> 00:04:43.360
And the practices of the church hopefully will come through in that.

62
00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:49.200
So we share, I'll go ahead and let you know, we share a common faith, a common life,

63
00:04:49.200 --> 00:04:50.680
and a common witness.

64
00:04:50.680 --> 00:04:55.360
Okay, so we share this common faith.

65
00:04:55.360 --> 00:04:57.520
Acts chapter two begins with the church.

66
00:04:57.520 --> 00:05:03.080
This made up of about 120 people, we're told, but by the end of it it now has over

67
00:05:03.080 --> 00:05:04.760
3,000 people.

68
00:05:04.760 --> 00:05:09.000
Now that is wonderful, but you can imagine all of the challenges that would come with

69
00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:10.000
that.

70
00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.600
I mean just imagine 3,000 people turning up this morning.

71
00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:16.600
We wouldn't know what to do with them, like how many people could we have in here at

72
00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:17.600
any given time.

73
00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:22.280
So the church is facing all kinds of challenges, no doubt from day one.

74
00:05:22.280 --> 00:05:25.800
The 120 people, remember, they had gotten to know one another pretty well.

75
00:05:25.800 --> 00:05:29.600
These were people who had already been following Jesus together.

76
00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:32.320
But they didn't know these other people very well.

77
00:05:32.320 --> 00:05:34.120
How can you get to know 3,000 people?

78
00:05:34.120 --> 00:05:38.040
And then the question then becomes, well, how can you know that they are part of the

79
00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:39.040
church?

80
00:05:39.040 --> 00:05:44.360
How can we be confident enough in these 3,000 people to say like, oh, the Lord has added

81
00:05:44.360 --> 00:05:47.440
them to our number as the church?

82
00:05:47.440 --> 00:05:51.320
Well, they can be confident, and here's why.

83
00:05:51.320 --> 00:05:56.200
It's because those people walked through the same door that they walked through to

84
00:05:56.200 --> 00:05:58.120
get into the church.

85
00:05:58.120 --> 00:06:00.840
And by that, I don't mean the buildings, they don't have a building they're

86
00:06:00.840 --> 00:06:03.120
walking into.

87
00:06:03.120 --> 00:06:07.320
So if you can imagine the life of the church happening inside a house, if you enter this

88
00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:11.160
house, you must come through the front door, all right?

89
00:06:11.160 --> 00:06:13.800
So what is this front door that they've all passed through?

90
00:06:13.800 --> 00:06:18.040
What's the, what's this common door that they've passed through into the common life of the

91
00:06:18.040 --> 00:06:19.520
church?

92
00:06:19.520 --> 00:06:23.960
Well, only God knows the hearts of those who initially walked through this door.

93
00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:28.360
But as far as the church is concerned, we need to be ready to welcome anybody

94
00:06:28.360 --> 00:06:30.080
who comes through this door.

95
00:06:30.080 --> 00:06:32.120
Okay, what is the door?

96
00:06:32.120 --> 00:06:33.640
The door is the gospel.

97
00:06:33.640 --> 00:06:35.720
The gospel is the door.

98
00:06:35.720 --> 00:06:41.920
Here we see that everyone who receives this gospel by faith and makes that public through

99
00:06:41.920 --> 00:06:47.360
baptism is recognized here as being part of the church.

100
00:06:47.360 --> 00:06:49.280
So let's see it together.

101
00:06:49.280 --> 00:06:54.320
Verse 41, the gospel has just been preached and it says, so those who received the

102
00:06:54.320 --> 00:07:05.040
word were baptized and they were added to that day, added that day about 3,000 souls.

103
00:07:05.040 --> 00:07:10.440
These people in verse 41 are the they that you then have in the verses following.

104
00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:11.440
So let's look at this together.

105
00:07:11.440 --> 00:07:13.680
So you see the gospel is received.

106
00:07:13.680 --> 00:07:15.120
They receive the word.

107
00:07:15.120 --> 00:07:20.480
Peter has just preached a message that centers on the person and work of Jesus.

108
00:07:20.480 --> 00:07:23.320
He preaches about Jesus' death.

109
00:07:23.320 --> 00:07:27.480
He preaches about His resurrection and His reign over all things.

110
00:07:27.480 --> 00:07:28.960
And the message is the same today.

111
00:07:28.960 --> 00:07:35.240
Though we have rebelled against God's reign over our lives, the King has come into the

112
00:07:35.240 --> 00:07:41.520
world and He has laid down His life on the cross so that rebels like us can be reconciled

113
00:07:41.520 --> 00:07:42.520
to God.

114
00:07:42.520 --> 00:07:47.040
So we've rebelled against God, but the King comes and instead of coming in wrath,

115
00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:52.640
He comes and lays down His life in mercy so that we can be welcomed to Himself.

116
00:07:52.640 --> 00:08:00.200
And today God still forgives anyone who will turn from their sin and put their trust in

117
00:08:00.200 --> 00:08:04.560
Jesus as their Savior and King.

118
00:08:04.560 --> 00:08:09.160
So those who have received Christ by faith are welcomed by God.

119
00:08:09.160 --> 00:08:14.400
And in being welcomed to God, they are welcomed into this community called the church.

120
00:08:14.400 --> 00:08:16.720
They've been welcomed by Him through Christ.

121
00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:21.360
You know, there's a longstanding tradition in church buildings where you get these old

122
00:08:21.360 --> 00:08:24.560
church buildings where the front door is painted red.

123
00:08:24.560 --> 00:08:29.160
And that's a kind of a picture of the gospel because we all enter the church by way of

124
00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:33.700
the cross through the death of Jesus for us.

125
00:08:33.700 --> 00:08:37.240
So if we receive this message by faith, we're welcomed by God and brought into the

126
00:08:37.240 --> 00:08:38.240
church.

127
00:08:38.240 --> 00:08:42.880
We've also got this other thing that's told us about being recognized as being part

128
00:08:42.880 --> 00:08:43.880
of the church.

129
00:08:43.880 --> 00:08:48.840
So you have the gospel is received, but the gospel is also portrayed here.

130
00:08:48.840 --> 00:08:52.640
It says those who received His Word were baptized.

131
00:08:52.640 --> 00:08:57.960
So we're talking about the practices of the church and that includes baptism.

132
00:08:57.960 --> 00:09:02.000
So those who received the Word and were baptized were recognized as having been added to

133
00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:03.000
the church.

134
00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:05.720
So what are we to make of this?

135
00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:09.000
Well, let's be clear.

136
00:09:09.000 --> 00:09:11.960
Baptism is not the gospel.

137
00:09:11.960 --> 00:09:13.000
It's not.

138
00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:15.280
So 1 Corinthians chapter 1 verse 17.

139
00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:18.400
Hear these words from the apostle Paul and the distinction here.

140
00:09:18.400 --> 00:09:24.360
He says, Christ did not send me to baptize but to preach the gospel.

141
00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:27.840
So there's the gospel that's received and there's baptism and they're not the same

142
00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:28.840
thing.

143
00:09:28.840 --> 00:09:31.280
So do you hear the distinction?

144
00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:34.960
We entered the church by the way of the cross.

145
00:09:34.960 --> 00:09:37.080
Period.

146
00:09:37.080 --> 00:09:43.880
But our entrance through that door is then made visible to others through baptism.

147
00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:50.920
Okay, so baptism is not the gospel, but baptism is a picture of the gospel.

148
00:09:50.920 --> 00:09:57.240
So those who trust in Christ are united to Him in His death and in His resurrection.

149
00:09:57.240 --> 00:10:02.240
And so in baptism, going under the water is like being buried with Christ and being

150
00:10:02.240 --> 00:10:06.800
raised up from the waters, like being risen with Him.

151
00:10:06.800 --> 00:10:11.680
So baptism is portraying our union with Jesus and His death and His resurrection.

152
00:10:11.680 --> 00:10:17.920
It's a sign and a symbol pointing to what Jesus has done for us.

153
00:10:17.920 --> 00:10:19.000
So this happens inwardly.

154
00:10:19.000 --> 00:10:21.520
It's an inward reality that's being united to Jesus.

155
00:10:21.520 --> 00:10:29.560
And then others see that as we are willing to proclaim that in baptism outwardly.

156
00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:30.720
This may help you.

157
00:10:30.720 --> 00:10:32.680
It helps me as a kind of illustration.

158
00:10:32.680 --> 00:10:36.640
When a man and a woman enter into the covenant of marriage, they are united together

159
00:10:36.680 --> 00:10:37.360
as ones.

160
00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:39.040
That's that kind of union.

161
00:10:39.040 --> 00:10:43.560
That marriage ceremony is accompanied by a symbol, right?

162
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:45.560
The exchanging of rings.

163
00:10:45.560 --> 00:10:46.880
I've got mine here.

164
00:10:46.880 --> 00:10:49.600
And so the ring isn't the thing that brings about.

165
00:10:49.600 --> 00:10:56.480
It doesn't cause their union with their spouse, but it is a public declaration of that union.

166
00:10:56.480 --> 00:11:01.920
And if somebody says, well, I don't really want to identify with my husband or my wife,

167
00:11:01.920 --> 00:11:06.520
you have to think something doesn't sound right there.

168
00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:10.760
Similarly in baptism, we are identifying with Christ.

169
00:11:10.760 --> 00:11:13.360
We're portraying our union with Him.

170
00:11:13.360 --> 00:11:18.360
And we're doing so in a way that He commanded because Jesus commanded His disciples.

171
00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:26.000
He said in Matthew 28, 19, go make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name

172
00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:29.040
of the Father, Son, and Holy Spirit.

173
00:11:29.040 --> 00:11:34.120
So if somebody is a disciple, they're following Jesus, they're identified with Him.

174
00:11:34.120 --> 00:11:36.320
They make that known through baptism.

175
00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:38.480
As they are entering the waters in that way.

176
00:11:38.480 --> 00:11:40.040
And this is the practice of the early church.

177
00:11:40.040 --> 00:11:45.120
As you read on in the book of Acts, you see baptisms happening when people respond in

178
00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:46.920
faith to the message of the gospel.

179
00:11:46.920 --> 00:11:52.880
They have that inward faith in Jesus, but this is expressed outwardly in baptism.

180
00:11:52.880 --> 00:11:57.840
So the church stands ready to identify with anyone who is ready to identify with

181
00:11:57.840 --> 00:12:00.800
Jesus in the way that He commanded.

182
00:12:00.800 --> 00:12:05.560
And at Trinity, we stand ready to do the same.

183
00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:12.680
We're ready to baptize anyone who has received Jesus as their Savior and King.

184
00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:14.920
And we don't have formal membership yet.

185
00:12:14.920 --> 00:12:18.960
Just so you know, that's the direction we are moving in, having formal membership

186
00:12:18.960 --> 00:12:20.240
in the church.

187
00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:25.280
And baptism will be part of that conversation in terms of being brought

188
00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:27.960
into the membership of the church.

189
00:12:27.960 --> 00:12:33.080
Now, recognize that raises questions and far more questions we can answer

190
00:12:33.080 --> 00:12:34.280
just like right now.

191
00:12:34.320 --> 00:12:36.800
And so I'm happy to talk with anybody about any questions they have in

192
00:12:36.800 --> 00:12:38.760
relation to this.

193
00:12:38.760 --> 00:12:41.760
But let me just address just some three quick ones here.

194
00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:47.040
One is, well, what if I have a different conviction about the mode of baptism?

195
00:12:47.040 --> 00:12:50.800
You know, I believe the gospel, but I hold to a different conviction.

196
00:12:50.800 --> 00:12:54.520
And I can take you to scripture to show you why I hold to that conviction.

197
00:12:54.520 --> 00:12:56.520
Let me just say, well, let's talk about that.

198
00:12:56.520 --> 00:12:59.280
And if somebody holds a different conviction, but they hold to the

199
00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:03.560
gospel and they've been baptized, we're willing to welcome them into

200
00:13:03.560 --> 00:13:07.360
the life of the church, even if the mode of baptism might have been different.

201
00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:10.920
But let's it's a conversation that we can certainly have.

202
00:13:10.920 --> 00:13:16.400
Another question is, is baptism really necessary?

203
00:13:16.400 --> 00:13:20.480
There's some who might not want to be baptized because it's a humbling

204
00:13:20.480 --> 00:13:24.160
experience that they would rather just avoid.

205
00:13:24.160 --> 00:13:29.040
But here's the thing, if Jesus is truly your Savior and King,

206
00:13:29.040 --> 00:13:33.160
he calls you to follow him and to follow him in this way.

207
00:13:33.200 --> 00:13:38.360
He's called us to identify with him in this way and know that baptism is such a

208
00:13:38.360 --> 00:13:41.240
joyful occasion.

209
00:13:41.240 --> 00:13:48.120
So yes, it is necessary because Jesus has told us to follow him in this way,

210
00:13:48.120 --> 00:13:50.240
to identify with him in this way.

211
00:13:50.240 --> 00:13:53.080
But another question may come up.

212
00:13:53.080 --> 00:13:56.400
Is am I am I good enough for baptism?

213
00:13:56.400 --> 00:13:59.760
May think, well, yeah, I believe that Jesus has died for me, but I look at

214
00:13:59.800 --> 00:14:03.480
my life and especially when I look at my sinfulness and I think, well,

215
00:14:03.480 --> 00:14:07.120
am I ready for baptism?

216
00:14:07.120 --> 00:14:10.080
If that's you know that when you come to the waters of baptism,

217
00:14:10.080 --> 00:14:14.120
you're not there to declare your goodness.

218
00:14:14.120 --> 00:14:17.240
When we come there, we're proclaiming that we are sinners,

219
00:14:17.240 --> 00:14:20.480
but Jesus died for sinners just like me.

220
00:14:20.480 --> 00:14:22.040
You don't come because you're good enough.

221
00:14:22.040 --> 00:14:25.720
You came because Jesus died for us.

222
00:14:25.720 --> 00:14:29.880
And so we're proclaiming that Jesus welcomed sinners just like us.

223
00:14:29.880 --> 00:14:35.200
It's not because we're good enough, but because of his gospel.

224
00:14:35.200 --> 00:14:39.160
So we have this common faith that we share together and that is faith in Christ.

225
00:14:39.160 --> 00:14:43.160
We make that known through baptism.

226
00:14:43.160 --> 00:14:46.520
But that faith is also seen in our life that we share together.

227
00:14:46.520 --> 00:14:49.640
So let's look at our common lives, our common faith.

228
00:14:49.640 --> 00:14:53.200
We have this faith in Christ and now we've walked through the door into the

229
00:14:53.200 --> 00:14:54.600
house, so to speak.

230
00:14:54.600 --> 00:14:58.880
So what does life look like inside this house called the church?

231
00:14:58.880 --> 00:15:00.040
A few brief things in passing.

232
00:15:00.040 --> 00:15:04.320
One is remember, this is a life that is brought about by the spirits.

233
00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:08.280
The practices that we're seeing isn't just like a list for us to kind of like

234
00:15:08.280 --> 00:15:09.000
mark off.

235
00:15:09.000 --> 00:15:13.440
It is evidence that the spirit of God is at work in his community,

236
00:15:13.440 --> 00:15:16.320
